4.3 Profiles The key assumption behind the exploitation of acquaintances" profiles, as it was originally proposed in [12,13], is that for an agent to pass a specific information item, this agent has a high interest on it or to related information.
Given a static setting where agents do not shift their expertise , and the distribution of information pieces does not change , the network will eventually reach a state where no information concerning agents '' information abilities will need to be propagated and no agents '' profiles will need to be updated : Queries shall be propagated only 